1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,075 --> 00:00:40,675
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,675 --> 00:00:42,085
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:44,215 --> 00:00:45,985
No way! This can't be happening!

5
00:00:47,085 --> 00:00:48,085
What's wrong, Mr. Ha?

6
00:00:53,895 --> 00:00:55,125
(Update 2: "Momo's mother, Hyun Ran Hee,
Suspected in Apparent Suicide")

7
00:00:58,095 --> 00:00:59,335
That's Geum Ba Ra for you.

8
00:00:59,335 --> 00:01:01,365
She's first on scene and gets top intel.
She's our rookie, too.

9
00:01:01,435 --> 00:01:02,965
What is going on?

10
00:01:03,105 --> 00:01:05,135
The secret engagement story just blew up.

11
00:01:05,205 --> 00:01:08,535
Gosh, someone's dying every day now.

12
00:01:08,605 --> 00:01:09,605
The third update is out.

13
00:01:12,275 --> 00:01:13,275
Hurry up!

14
00:01:27,755 --> 00:01:29,825
Ma'am, it's dangerous.
Come on, what are you doing?

15
00:01:30,795 --> 00:01:33,865
- Gosh, Chief!
- You're relentless. Seriously.

16
00:01:49,045 --> 00:01:51,585
(Unpo Police Station)

17
00:02:02,365 --> 00:02:03,365
Excuse me.

18
00:02:04,325 --> 00:02:06,635
Do you have someone to help
around the house?

19
00:02:07,935 --> 00:02:09,765
Who does the cleaning...

20
00:02:11,235 --> 00:02:13,535
Was it just you and your mother
living here?

21
00:02:19,775 --> 00:02:22,145
Shouldn't you have rushed her
to the hospital?

22
00:02:22,445 --> 00:02:24,685
You didn't even perform CPR.

23
00:02:25,815 --> 00:02:27,815
It was too late for CPR.

24
00:02:28,385 --> 00:02:30,455
You just end up breaking their ribs
at that point.

25
00:02:36,525 --> 00:02:37,865
- Should we move her?
- Yes.

26
00:02:41,195 --> 00:02:43,465
Mom!

27
00:02:45,935 --> 00:02:47,235
- We're going in.
- You can't enter.

28
00:02:47,305 --> 00:02:48,635
We're close to her in both work and life.

29
00:02:48,635 --> 00:02:50,505
- If we can't go in, who can?
- Let us go in.

30
00:02:51,245 --> 00:02:52,245
We're practically family.

31
00:02:53,315 --> 00:02:55,445
- Who's in charge here?
- The police!

32
00:02:56,615 --> 00:02:57,845
Just give us one comment!

33
00:02:57,845 --> 00:02:59,115
- Hey, let us through.
- Yes. sir.

34
00:03:02,985 --> 00:03:04,285
- Is that confirmed, Chief?
- Look over here!

35
00:03:04,355 --> 00:03:05,355
- Make way!
- Step back!

36
00:03:20,705 --> 00:03:21,705
It's me.

37
00:03:25,505 --> 00:03:26,515
Are we sure it's a suicide?

38
00:03:26,815 --> 00:03:28,315
- Yes.
- Cause of death?

39
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,745
- Hypothermia, most likely.
- Hypothermia?

40
00:03:30,815 --> 00:03:32,355
The bedroom's an absolute freezer.

41
00:03:32,485 --> 00:03:33,615
The AC was...

42
00:03:37,325 --> 00:03:38,655
This is not the time or place!

43
00:04:09,585 --> 00:04:10,585
They're coming out!

44
00:04:32,815 --> 00:04:33,815
Momo.

45
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:56,505
Hello.

46
00:04:58,105 --> 00:05:00,905
You must be Momo's mother,
CEO Hyun Ran Hee.

47
00:05:11,485 --> 00:05:12,485
Ba Ra.

48
00:05:13,055 --> 00:05:14,915
- You actually came.
- Of course.

49
00:05:15,185 --> 00:05:16,325
Your mother is here too.

50
00:05:16,785 --> 00:05:17,785
Goodness.

51
00:05:19,925 --> 00:05:20,995
Ms. Hyun.

52
00:05:21,695 --> 00:05:23,225
I didn't expect to see you here.

53
00:05:23,825 --> 00:05:24,925
Neither did I.

54
00:05:25,425 --> 00:05:26,435
What brings you here?

55
00:05:26,695 --> 00:05:28,295
This is Geum Ba Ra,
a reporter from Sungwoo Daily.

56
00:05:29,535 --> 00:05:31,335
- Hello.
- Hello.

57
00:05:31,705 --> 00:05:35,035
She's covering the exhibition today,
and my schedule just happened to be free.

58
00:05:37,445 --> 00:05:39,245
Are you close with CEO Ju Yeong Ae?

59
00:05:40,175 --> 00:05:42,715
No. My senior editor sent me to cover it.

60
00:05:42,915 --> 00:05:44,715
Mom, do you have an exhibition coming up?

61
00:05:44,715 --> 00:05:45,815
It's in the works.

62
00:05:46,115 --> 00:05:47,515
- That's Momo, right?
- Yes.

63
00:05:47,915 --> 00:05:49,455
She's so much prettier in person.

64
00:05:50,485 --> 00:05:51,485
I'll be back.

65
00:05:55,255 --> 00:05:56,925
Look at CEO Ju, schmoozing.

66
00:06:11,745 --> 00:06:14,275
You can't just disappear on me
like last time.

67
00:06:15,245 --> 00:06:16,545
Chairman Kang has arrived.

68
00:06:16,545 --> 00:06:17,645
- Welcome.
- It's my pleasure.

69
00:06:18,985 --> 00:06:20,015
Excuse me for a moment.

70
00:06:25,825 --> 00:06:26,825
Hello.

71
00:06:29,295 --> 00:06:30,565
This is my daughter.

72
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:33,365
Artist Paul Kim. He was based in Germany.

73
00:06:33,965 --> 00:06:34,965
It's a pleasure to meet you.

74
00:06:36,065 --> 00:06:37,065
Hello.

75
00:06:37,565 --> 00:06:40,205
Your pieces have already sold, you know.
Both of them.

76
00:06:43,045 --> 00:06:45,405
She's a close reporter friend of mine
from Sungwoo Daily.

77
00:06:48,015 --> 00:06:50,945
- Excuse me. Is Artist Paul Kim here?
- Yes.

78
00:06:51,645 --> 00:06:54,285
- That's him.
- How's your work coming along?

79
00:06:54,585 --> 00:06:55,685
It's been a little slow lately.

80
00:06:56,385 --> 00:06:58,685
What do you do to relax?
Besides photography trips?

81
00:06:59,355 --> 00:07:00,995
I just read books and whatnot.

82
00:07:02,995 --> 00:07:04,395
Korea's changed a lot, hasn't it?

83
00:07:05,395 --> 00:07:07,395
Have you been back much?

84
00:07:07,735 --> 00:07:08,765
No.

85
00:07:09,635 --> 00:07:10,705
She doesn't look like you.

86
00:07:13,335 --> 00:07:15,075
An improvement on the original, right?

87
00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:18,075
I've never met her,
but I'm told I look like my grandmother.

88
00:07:20,075 --> 00:07:22,645
Excuse me, could I get a picture?

89
00:07:25,885 --> 00:07:27,015
Thank you.

90
00:07:28,215 --> 00:07:30,085
Give me a call next time you're in Seoul.

91
00:07:30,425 --> 00:07:31,585
You must be busy, though.

92
00:07:31,585 --> 00:07:33,425
It's fine as long as it's not last-minute.

93
00:07:35,895 --> 00:07:37,165
This is Artist Paul Kim.

94
00:07:38,695 --> 00:07:41,635
Hello. I'm Geum Ba Ra
from the Culture Desk at Sungwoo Daily.

95
00:07:43,105 --> 00:07:45,935
- Hi. I don't have a card yet.
- Please.

96
00:07:45,935 --> 00:07:47,805
Your work is your business card.

97
00:07:50,645 --> 00:07:52,445
Would you mind telling me a little
about your piece?

98
00:07:57,445 --> 00:07:58,615
Let me just get a picture first.

99
00:07:58,985 --> 00:08:00,785
I'm not planning to run the story
right away.

100
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:07,925
You'll get fans after this photo gets out,
won't you?

101
00:08:36,925 --> 00:08:37,925
What about the suicide note?

102
00:08:40,755 --> 00:08:43,225
- The forensics team has it.
- What does it say?

103
00:08:50,435 --> 00:08:52,605
(Emergency Medical Center)

104
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:03,145
- What happened?
- It appears to be a suicide.

105
00:09:03,215 --> 00:09:04,215
Okay, right this way.

106
00:10:52,725 --> 00:10:55,625
Ma'am, we're going to need you
to come down to the station.

107
00:10:59,835 --> 00:11:03,005
- We'll confirm with handwriting analysis.
- Understood.

108
00:11:03,065 --> 00:11:06,835
Check the gallery office, not the house,
for any documents handwritten by Ms. Hyun.

109
00:11:07,075 --> 00:11:08,105
Got it.

110
00:11:08,705 --> 00:11:10,805
Let me see the suicide note.
I won't write it in the article.

111
00:11:11,405 --> 00:11:13,315
You've already gotten your scoop.

112
00:11:16,945 --> 00:11:17,985
Go in my office.

113
00:11:17,985 --> 00:11:19,415
Reporters will be
swarming in here any minute.

114
00:11:23,355 --> 00:11:26,795
I can't imagine how you're feeling,
but we need to get your statement.

115
00:11:29,565 --> 00:11:31,325
Can you walk us through what happened?

116
00:11:31,965 --> 00:11:33,595
What time did you find her?

117
00:11:35,565 --> 00:11:36,805
I don't know.

118
00:11:37,335 --> 00:11:40,705
I didn't have anything scheduled today,
so I slept in a little.

119
00:11:44,705 --> 00:11:45,875
And when I woke up,

120
00:11:48,145 --> 00:11:49,345
it was quiet,

121
00:11:50,585 --> 00:11:52,515
so I figured she had gone to the gallery.

122
00:11:59,995 --> 00:12:02,595
How'd you know to call?
I literally just walked in.

123
00:12:03,665 --> 00:12:04,895
James just told me.

124
00:12:05,495 --> 00:12:06,795
Do you have plans for Christmas Eve?

125
00:12:06,795 --> 00:12:08,295
You know I don't make any special plans.

126
00:12:08,695 --> 00:12:10,905
I always have dinner with you
on Christmas Eve.

127
00:12:12,005 --> 00:12:13,675
We're thicker than blood, I swear.

128
00:12:13,805 --> 00:12:15,405
Does just sharing blood make you family?

129
00:12:15,575 --> 00:12:16,575
Exactly.

130
00:12:17,145 --> 00:12:18,745
Because plenty of siblings
are worse than strangers.

131
00:12:18,805 --> 00:12:19,975
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

132
00:12:20,045 --> 00:12:21,315
You should do a talent donation this time.

133
00:12:22,015 --> 00:12:23,385
What talent do I even have?

134
00:12:23,445 --> 00:12:26,385
Perform at the Sponsor Appreciation Night
at Nua Children's Home.

135
00:12:26,385 --> 00:12:27,655
My fingers are stiff now.

136
00:12:27,715 --> 00:12:29,115
They'll loosen up if you practice.

137
00:12:29,785 --> 00:12:31,255
It'd be great if James could come too.

138
00:12:31,485 --> 00:12:33,455
(Auditorium)

139
00:12:33,525 --> 00:12:34,755
Come on, let's go.

140
00:12:39,835 --> 00:12:42,165
- Hello.
- We keep running into each other.

141
00:12:42,265 --> 00:12:44,605
- It's not over, is it?
- Part two is about to start.

142
00:12:45,535 --> 00:12:48,605
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

143
00:12:53,315 --> 00:12:55,045
- Thank you.
- I'm a huge fan.

144
00:12:59,615 --> 00:13:01,385
- Hello.
- Hello.

145
00:13:01,785 --> 00:13:03,125
Are you enjoying the food?

146
00:13:18,335 --> 00:13:21,335
(Nua General Hospital)

147
00:13:22,535 --> 00:13:24,205
Do you come to this every year?

148
00:13:24,745 --> 00:13:25,745
Yes.

149
00:13:28,275 --> 00:13:31,185
The vibe here is so great with the music.

150
00:13:34,785 --> 00:13:36,115
You're drinking quite a bit today.

151
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:38,055
It's Christmas Eve.

152
00:13:38,855 --> 00:13:40,755
Next year, I'll keep my schedule clear,

153
00:13:40,755 --> 00:13:43,065
come early, and have a meal with the kids.

154
00:13:43,595 --> 00:13:44,595
You definitely should.

155
00:13:59,275 --> 00:14:00,675
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

156
00:15:54,295 --> 00:15:55,855
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

157
00:16:23,825 --> 00:16:26,025
(Nua Children's Home)

158
00:16:37,865 --> 00:16:39,165
(Nua Children's Home)

159
00:16:39,235 --> 00:16:40,975
- How'd the surgery go?
- It went well.

160
00:16:40,975 --> 00:16:43,345
The Chairman is on a call
with Ambassador Yu Gu Jong.

161
00:16:43,345 --> 00:16:45,405
All right. Is Momo here yet?

162
00:16:45,545 --> 00:16:47,915
Yes, she's a big hit with our guests.

163
00:16:52,085 --> 00:16:53,415
I'm so jealous.

164
00:16:53,485 --> 00:16:56,015
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

165
00:17:03,225 --> 00:17:04,325
You're here.

166
00:17:04,665 --> 00:17:07,035
- Advisor.
- Where's your father?

167
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:10,865
- Advisor!
- What is it?

168
00:17:10,935 --> 00:17:12,405
- What's going on?
- Advisor!

169
00:17:19,275 --> 00:17:20,745
Are you adopting another one?

170
00:17:23,015 --> 00:17:24,015
No.

171
00:17:25,145 --> 00:17:28,015
- It's not been long since Oiji passed.
- Where are you?

172
00:17:28,785 --> 00:17:29,855
Here.

173
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:36,225
I thought you'd be pulling an all-nighter
with Ju Shin.

174
00:17:36,525 --> 00:17:38,425
Momo's sponsored by your company, right?

175
00:17:38,725 --> 00:17:40,695
- Yes.
- Introduce me.

176
00:17:40,765 --> 00:17:42,565
- Was Momo at the party too?
- Yes.

177
00:17:43,465 --> 00:17:46,505
Forget about it.
She's getting engaged to Ju Shin soon.

178
00:17:48,935 --> 00:17:49,945
Really?

179
00:17:50,345 --> 00:17:51,345
Yes.

180
00:17:53,645 --> 00:17:56,815
- Did you introduce them?
- Ju Shin is head over heels for her.

181
00:17:57,215 --> 00:18:00,955
That's why Momo's here.
She'll be the foundation's first lady.

182
00:18:04,185 --> 00:18:06,695
Go have a cold beer to cool off
instead of just water.

183
00:18:08,895 --> 00:18:10,125
How are things between you and Eun Ah?

184
00:18:14,735 --> 00:18:17,405
Of all people, Momo?
I'm on Team Geum Ba Ra.

185
00:18:42,495 --> 00:18:43,495
Hello.

186
00:18:48,465 --> 00:18:49,465
It's cold out here.

187
00:18:49,965 --> 00:18:51,265
It's too hot inside.

188
00:18:52,665 --> 00:18:55,975
I made a fool of myself the other day.
I didn't know you were Ju Shin's friend.

189
00:18:57,245 --> 00:18:59,915
I got carried away hearing live music
for the first time in a while.

190
00:19:01,815 --> 00:19:02,945
Do you have a side gig?

191
00:19:04,215 --> 00:19:05,615
I'm not good enough to moonlight.

192
00:19:06,685 --> 00:19:08,515
I'm so jealous of people
who can play an instrument.

193
00:19:09,155 --> 00:19:11,825
- You could just learn.
- Then you can tutor me part-time.

194
00:19:15,855 --> 00:19:16,965
Where's Ju Shin?

195
00:19:17,725 --> 00:19:19,935
- The restroom.
- Is his stomach acting up again?

196
00:19:20,235 --> 00:19:23,165
Yes.
And he only had juice on the way over.

197
00:19:24,265 --> 00:19:25,865
I guess that's
how the skies keep things fair.

198
00:19:25,865 --> 00:19:27,535
Ju Shin has a weak stomach,

199
00:19:28,275 --> 00:19:29,805
but he's an A-plus in every other way.

200
00:19:33,845 --> 00:19:34,945
I'm Ha Yong Joong, by the way.

201
00:19:35,315 --> 00:19:39,585
With the Advisor collapsing that day,
Ju Shin never got to introduce us.

202
00:19:41,115 --> 00:19:42,215
I'm Momo.

203
00:19:42,215 --> 00:19:44,855
I looked you up. It's your real name.

204
00:19:45,525 --> 00:19:48,025
Yes,
a lot of people assume it's a stage name.

205
00:19:49,865 --> 00:19:51,295
So why did you look me up?

206
00:19:54,965 --> 00:19:56,135
Curious about me as an actress?

207
00:19:57,905 --> 00:19:59,465
Or as your friend's girlfriend?

208
00:20:02,435 --> 00:20:04,375
Both, of course.

209
00:20:09,245 --> 00:20:11,015
I hear you've been very busy.

210
00:20:11,345 --> 00:20:14,255
I was away for a while,
so I have a lot to catch up on.

211
00:20:14,455 --> 00:20:17,525
Everyone's been swamped.
Especially Ju Shin, of course.

212
00:20:19,425 --> 00:20:20,495
Ju Shin...

213
00:20:21,455 --> 00:20:23,465
never really showed much interest
in women before.

214
00:20:24,665 --> 00:20:27,135
I even started to wonder
if he had a crush on me.

215
00:20:38,645 --> 00:20:39,645
It's all set.

216
00:20:41,415 --> 00:20:42,415
What do you mean?

217
00:20:44,745 --> 00:20:45,915
You seem happy.

218
00:20:49,455 --> 00:20:50,885
Do you have any jinxes, by any chance?

219
00:20:51,955 --> 00:20:53,085
What kind of jinx?

220
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,955
The kind that makes you want to dance.

221
00:20:55,655 --> 00:20:57,365
If only music were playing now...

222
00:20:57,725 --> 00:20:59,825
I have the sudden urge to waltz right now.

223
00:21:03,435 --> 00:21:04,435
With me?

224
00:21:06,365 --> 00:21:07,375
Yes.

225
00:21:58,555 --> 00:22:01,555
Spring is right around the corner,
and yet a blizzard hit us.

226
00:22:02,395 --> 00:22:03,795
You know how to waltz?

227
00:22:04,965 --> 00:22:05,995
I am an actress, after all.

228
00:22:06,865 --> 00:22:08,365
I can sort of pull off the tango too.

229
00:22:09,265 --> 00:22:12,265
I wish I'd learned it
for a day like today.

230
00:22:14,735 --> 00:22:17,275
I heard your mother was
a double bass player.

231
00:22:17,745 --> 00:22:18,745
She was.

232
00:22:19,945 --> 00:22:20,945
Ju Shin...

233
00:22:21,545 --> 00:22:23,685
didn't just say good things about me,
did he?

234
00:22:25,045 --> 00:22:26,855
He said you were
his most troublesome friend.

235
00:22:33,525 --> 00:22:35,425
Is my makeup too much?

236
00:22:37,195 --> 00:22:38,195
No.

237
00:22:48,635 --> 00:22:49,775
Why are you standing out here?

238
00:22:52,605 --> 00:22:54,415
It's hot in this dress.

239
00:22:56,475 --> 00:22:59,245
(Our deepest condolences
to the bereaved family)

240
00:23:29,315 --> 00:23:30,315
(Family waiting room)

241
00:23:39,025 --> 00:23:41,055
Push my meeting with Mr. Jo to tomorrow.

242
00:23:41,795 --> 00:23:44,165
- The cross shoot is at 3 p.m.
- Send Manager Choi.

243
00:23:45,195 --> 00:23:47,895
- Let's go pay our respects, Jin Ju.
- I've already been.

244
00:23:48,235 --> 00:23:50,335
- When?
- Last night.

245
00:23:56,945 --> 00:23:57,945
Momo.

246
00:23:59,205 --> 00:24:00,375
Did I do the right thing?

247
00:24:01,545 --> 00:24:02,945
Do I really have to let you go like this?

248
00:25:16,085 --> 00:25:17,225
Do you think you'll be able to sleep?

249
00:25:18,525 --> 00:25:20,595
Just talk to me like you talk to Momo.

250
00:25:20,995 --> 00:25:22,195
If anyone heard you...

251
00:25:22,555 --> 00:25:24,165
It's not like we'll be seeing each other
much longer anyway.

252
00:25:29,795 --> 00:25:32,135
You can say you broke up naturally
by next year anyway.

253
00:25:35,105 --> 00:25:36,105
Go.

254
00:25:38,445 --> 00:25:40,415
I'm going to keep drinking
until I fall asleep.

255
00:25:42,475 --> 00:25:44,345
I'm really starting to feel
like I'm becoming Momo.

256
00:25:45,045 --> 00:25:48,655
She's not some stranger.
She's my own flesh and blood.

257
00:25:49,455 --> 00:25:52,785
I am Momo, and Momo is me.

258
00:25:56,355 --> 00:25:57,865
Puppies and wine...

259
00:25:58,425 --> 00:26:00,435
are the deity's gift to humanity.

260
00:26:07,035 --> 00:26:08,035
You're not having any?

261
00:26:08,305 --> 00:26:09,475
I drove.

262
00:26:09,735 --> 00:26:11,045
We can call for a ride.

263
00:26:15,275 --> 00:26:16,575
When I look in the mirror,

264
00:26:16,985 --> 00:26:18,915
it doesn't feel like Momo's dead.

265
00:26:20,015 --> 00:26:24,155
It just feels like
I'm looking right at my daughter.

266
00:26:27,595 --> 00:26:28,955
Hyun Ran Hee is the one who died.

267
00:26:31,425 --> 00:26:33,095
They say there's more than meets the eye,

268
00:26:33,635 --> 00:26:35,665
you should just accept what you see.

269
00:26:36,335 --> 00:26:38,005
There's no need to overthink it.

270
00:26:45,545 --> 00:26:46,845
It's too quiet.

271
00:26:52,015 --> 00:26:54,285
He has such a noble brow.

272
00:26:54,985 --> 00:26:56,855
So aristocratic.

273
00:26:57,355 --> 00:26:59,085
Like fine white porcelain.

274
00:27:01,825 --> 00:27:02,825
Leaving?

275
00:27:07,035 --> 00:27:08,535
Loosen your tie before you go.

276
00:27:08,865 --> 00:27:10,465
It looks so tight and suffocating.

277
00:27:39,625 --> 00:27:40,995
Go abroad for a while.

278
00:27:41,765 --> 00:27:42,765
It's me.

279
00:27:46,035 --> 00:27:47,235
Why on earth?

280
00:27:48,335 --> 00:27:50,005
(CEO James Ha)

281
00:27:51,945 --> 00:27:54,675
- Hello?
- Hi, it's James.

282
00:27:54,875 --> 00:27:56,175
Mr. Ha. Hello.

283
00:27:56,375 --> 00:28:00,215
With Momo's mother away,
I'm sure you don't have an appetite.

284
00:28:00,415 --> 00:28:02,585
I figured you'd be starving at home alone,

285
00:28:02,655 --> 00:28:04,125
so I made some side dishes.

286
00:28:04,925 --> 00:28:08,125
Sending them by a manager felt impersonal,
and I was worried about you.

287
00:28:08,955 --> 00:28:09,955
I see.

288
00:28:10,665 --> 00:28:12,825
Would it be alright if I dropped by?

289
00:28:13,225 --> 00:28:15,765
They aren't dishes we have to eat today,
are they?

290
00:28:15,835 --> 00:28:17,065
Of course not.

291
00:28:17,335 --> 00:28:18,665
Are you on your way home?

292
00:28:19,035 --> 00:28:20,405
Are you off work yet?

293
00:28:20,705 --> 00:28:21,805
I'm about to.

294
00:28:23,235 --> 00:28:24,245
Have a seat.

295
00:28:26,875 --> 00:28:28,745
Do you have any food at home?

296
00:28:29,545 --> 00:28:31,985
I'm not that interested in food.

297
00:28:32,645 --> 00:28:36,455
Why not? Eating is extremely important.

298
00:28:38,285 --> 00:28:39,785
That's no good.

299
00:28:39,785 --> 00:28:42,255
Eat well in your youth to age well.

300
00:28:42,355 --> 00:28:46,065
- Hippocrates said it best.
- "You are what you eat"?

301
00:28:46,125 --> 00:28:47,135
Exactly.

302
00:28:50,965 --> 00:28:52,505
Do you have a dog?

303
00:28:53,365 --> 00:28:55,205
I lost her, the year before last.

304
00:29:01,745 --> 00:29:03,315
Do you like dogs?

305
00:29:03,915 --> 00:29:05,115
Of course.

306
00:29:05,945 --> 00:29:07,555
Her name was Oiji?

307
00:29:08,255 --> 00:29:09,785
They give out awards for this?

308
00:29:10,525 --> 00:29:11,555
Yes.

309
00:29:11,755 --> 00:29:14,025
She had been through a lot.

310
00:29:26,265 --> 00:29:27,735
I think I taste some lemon.

311
00:29:27,805 --> 00:29:29,805
That, and some other healthy stuff.

312
00:29:30,135 --> 00:29:31,575
Stay for a quick dinner.

313
00:29:31,805 --> 00:29:34,815
- No, I'm fine.
- It's no trouble. It's already made.

314
00:30:02,635 --> 00:30:05,905
It's not from a package.
I slow-cooked it with premium beef.

315
00:30:06,045 --> 00:30:07,515
You're so busy, but you made it yourself?

316
00:30:07,575 --> 00:30:09,375
They say, "If you want it done right,
do it yourself."

317
00:30:10,275 --> 00:30:11,515
I've heard that one.

318
00:30:12,015 --> 00:30:13,185
Add salt if you need it.

319
00:30:17,985 --> 00:30:19,155
Thank you for the meal.

320
00:30:25,025 --> 00:30:26,725
- It's not bland at all.
- Good.

321
00:30:26,725 --> 00:30:28,765
It's perfect. I actually prefer less salt.

322
00:30:28,835 --> 00:30:30,765
That's the way to do it.

323
00:30:37,345 --> 00:30:39,675
Wouldn't it be nice to live this way?

324
00:30:39,675 --> 00:30:41,345
I'd treat her like a queen,

325
00:30:41,415 --> 00:30:43,245
and she wouldn't have to lift a finger.

326
00:30:48,685 --> 00:30:50,855
Gosh, look how she enjoys her food.

327
00:30:52,955 --> 00:30:55,825
She didn't seem depressed at all.

328
00:30:56,455 --> 00:31:00,365
Right. Maybe if her career
as Momo was failing...

329
00:31:00,865 --> 00:31:04,035
- She was about to get married...
- I know.

330
00:31:04,035 --> 00:31:05,205
She had a top-star daughter,

331
00:31:05,265 --> 00:31:07,905
who was engaged to a catch
like Director Shin,

332
00:31:07,905 --> 00:31:09,305
and her gallery was doing well.

333
00:31:09,575 --> 00:31:11,775
Do you think having no worries
is a problem in itself?

334
00:31:13,205 --> 00:31:14,645
How is Momo getting by?

335
00:31:17,315 --> 00:31:18,315
By the way,

336
00:31:18,645 --> 00:31:21,815
since you're Yong Joong's older brother,
you don't have to be so formal with me.

337
00:31:22,855 --> 00:31:24,885
- You sure?
- Yes.

338
00:31:24,955 --> 00:31:27,455
That makes sense,
since you're so close with Yong Joong.

339
00:31:29,125 --> 00:31:31,065
Maybe she'll feel that way with me.

340
00:31:32,725 --> 00:31:35,665
- Ha Yong Joong's car is now arriving.
- He's here for the side dishes.

341
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:39,365
It's all the same stuff, so take one each.

342
00:31:39,665 --> 00:31:43,575
- One for me too?
- They're better if you make a big batch.

343
00:31:43,705 --> 00:31:46,105
I'll drop Ba Ra off and take this to Momo.

344
00:31:46,605 --> 00:31:47,615
And why would you do that?

345
00:31:48,075 --> 00:31:50,445
- Does Ba Ra even have her car here?
- She can take a cab.

346
00:31:50,745 --> 00:31:51,745
Right?

347
00:31:52,685 --> 00:31:54,755
You're going to make a reporter
run errands for an actress?

348
00:31:54,815 --> 00:31:57,115
Their jobs have nothing to do with it.
They were close friends.

349
00:31:57,625 --> 00:31:58,685
Weren't you?

350
00:32:00,225 --> 00:32:03,965
- Anyway.
- She's alone at home with no helper.

351
00:32:04,195 --> 00:32:06,195
I can just ask her
to come down to the lobby.

352
00:32:06,425 --> 00:32:10,165
Is Momo just some random person?
What if Ju Shin gets the wrong idea?

353
00:32:10,235 --> 00:32:12,465
It could get awkward for Momo too.

354
00:32:12,805 --> 00:32:14,335
It's just an errand for you.
What's the big deal?

355
00:32:15,035 --> 00:32:18,075
I didn't ask you to. Leave me out of it.
Fine then.

356
00:32:18,875 --> 00:32:20,545
I'll just eat it myself then. Forget it.

357
00:32:21,815 --> 00:32:24,315
I think he's just worried about her.

358
00:32:24,685 --> 00:32:26,445
That's my point.

359
00:32:26,445 --> 00:32:28,655
Why is he so worried
about his best friend's fiancee?

360
00:32:28,715 --> 00:32:30,655
Ju Shin will take care of her.

361
00:32:30,655 --> 00:32:32,225
You think Ju Shin cooks and cleans?

362
00:32:32,525 --> 00:32:33,655
You think he has time?

363
00:32:33,655 --> 00:32:35,295
- If he had three bodies...
- And you?

364
00:32:35,625 --> 00:32:36,655
Do you have time?

365
00:32:36,725 --> 00:32:38,395
Imagine how hard it must be
for her right now.

366
00:32:39,325 --> 00:32:40,735
We went through it too.

367
00:32:41,535 --> 00:32:42,535
Have you forgotten?

368
00:32:47,005 --> 00:32:49,305
Let's go see her tomorrow morning.

369
00:32:49,535 --> 00:32:51,345
I can't just ignore this either.

370
00:32:51,675 --> 00:32:53,505
It's too late tonight.

371
00:33:06,555 --> 00:33:07,555
Her address.

372
00:33:14,965 --> 00:33:16,165
You don't get it either, do you?

373
00:33:31,915 --> 00:33:34,085
Sorry, all I have is water and coffee.

374
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:37,155
I'm thirsty.

375
00:33:51,405 --> 00:33:52,405
That guy...

376
00:33:53,065 --> 00:33:54,675
He's been doing better than I expected.

377
00:33:57,175 --> 00:33:58,945
Being a bodyguard pays pretty well.

378
00:34:00,375 --> 00:34:01,575
It's hazard pay.

379
00:34:04,185 --> 00:34:06,185
Once I get the new place,
I'll sell this place...

380
00:34:06,185 --> 00:34:08,185
and donate the money in An Hee's name.

381
00:34:09,955 --> 00:34:11,655
You know I can help you out.

382
00:34:14,795 --> 00:34:16,495
Am I treating you differently from An Hee?

383
00:34:18,165 --> 00:34:20,995
I've faced so much discrimination,
I don't want to even hear that word.

384
00:34:24,665 --> 00:34:26,335
Lawyer Tae Won Young said he knew you.

385
00:34:29,075 --> 00:34:30,635
I signed a contract with his law firm,

386
00:34:31,175 --> 00:34:32,675
and while we were talking
about that interview article...

387
00:34:35,775 --> 00:34:37,715
I heard he got remarried.

388
00:34:39,715 --> 00:34:40,915
Is he happy?

389
00:34:41,415 --> 00:34:42,485
He's remarried?

390
00:34:43,485 --> 00:34:46,155
- What did he say about me?
- Nothing really.

391
00:34:46,155 --> 00:34:48,095
An associate was there.

392
00:34:48,495 --> 00:34:49,795
Do you two have some kind of history?

393
00:35:06,105 --> 00:35:07,545
Are you Ye Jeong's father?

394
00:35:07,575 --> 00:35:08,615
Yes.

395
00:35:10,345 --> 00:35:11,585
I'm here because of Ye Jeong.

396
00:35:12,715 --> 00:35:14,915
I was on my way to the police station,
but I came here instead.

397
00:35:18,385 --> 00:35:19,425
Ye Jeong!

398
00:35:20,455 --> 00:35:22,825
Your father said
he was going to bed early.

399
00:35:22,895 --> 00:35:24,125
Tell her to come downstairs.

400
00:35:35,505 --> 00:35:36,505
Sit.

401
00:35:39,205 --> 00:35:40,605
Let's talk about this inside.

402
00:35:46,115 --> 00:35:47,685
- I'm home, Father.
- Alright.

403
00:35:49,685 --> 00:35:50,685
Who are you?

404
00:35:52,985 --> 00:35:54,295
My name is Geum Ba Ra.

405
00:35:54,825 --> 00:35:56,655
I'm not in the same class
as Tae Ye Jeong, though.

406
00:36:05,065 --> 00:36:06,335
Sit down, all of you.

407
00:36:08,175 --> 00:36:09,675
Bring something out.

408
00:36:10,275 --> 00:36:11,275
I'm fine.

409
00:36:16,545 --> 00:36:18,785
I grew up at an orphanage...

410
00:36:18,785 --> 00:36:20,585
with a girl from my class, Kim Jin Ju.

411
00:36:21,315 --> 00:36:23,455
Do you know Nua Children's Home?

412
00:36:23,855 --> 00:36:25,755
The one behind the cathedral?

413
00:36:26,125 --> 00:36:30,095
Yes. Jin Ju and I have been roommates
our whole lives,

414
00:36:30,625 --> 00:36:32,995
but Tae Ye Jeong constantly bullies her.

415
00:36:32,995 --> 00:36:35,565
Today, she even hit her with two others.

416
00:36:38,235 --> 00:36:40,365
- It's over and done with.
- How can it be over?

417
00:36:40,435 --> 00:36:41,535
I ended it.

418
00:36:41,635 --> 00:36:43,435
But you're the one
who started this up again.

419
00:36:44,005 --> 00:36:46,305
- I got hit too!
- Quiet!

420
00:36:48,145 --> 00:36:49,875
I saw the three of them
ganging up on Jin Ju,

421
00:36:49,945 --> 00:36:52,945
so I had no choice but to hit them
a few times to defend her.

422
00:36:53,615 --> 00:36:55,755
They started coming after me too.
What was I supposed to do?

423
00:36:56,355 --> 00:36:58,355
Growing up in an orphanage
is already hard enough,

424
00:36:58,785 --> 00:37:00,355
and it's a painful wound.

425
00:37:02,195 --> 00:37:05,625
But they ridiculed us,
calling us brats with no parents.

426
00:37:06,595 --> 00:37:08,435
But I endured it and put an end to it.

427
00:37:10,195 --> 00:37:13,265
Did you know your daughter bullies kids
who are easy targets?

428
00:37:15,505 --> 00:37:16,535
I didn't even...

429
00:37:17,475 --> 00:37:18,775
That's not what a student does.

430
00:37:19,005 --> 00:37:21,345
She does monstrous things
without a second thought.

431
00:37:21,615 --> 00:37:24,785
Have you ever thought about what it's like
to be on the receiving end?

432
00:37:24,785 --> 00:37:25,785
You're lying.

433
00:37:27,115 --> 00:37:28,985
- Don't exaggerate.
- You think I'm exaggerating?

434
00:37:29,385 --> 00:37:30,385
So...

435
00:37:30,715 --> 00:37:33,885
Are you saying my Ye Jeong
did this to you?

436
00:37:35,395 --> 00:37:36,455
Her "husband" did.

437
00:37:36,895 --> 00:37:37,895
Hey!

438
00:37:39,865 --> 00:37:41,795
It's just a stupid joke
among the kids at school.

439
00:37:41,865 --> 00:37:43,565
I heard it clearly. Yoon Seong Tae.

440
00:37:43,565 --> 00:37:44,865
He's a senior at our school,

441
00:37:45,035 --> 00:37:46,805
and he said,
"You scratched my wife's face."

442
00:37:46,805 --> 00:37:47,835
What...

443
00:37:47,835 --> 00:37:48,905
Father.

444
00:37:51,905 --> 00:37:54,075
He's just an older guy
who tends to overreact.

445
00:37:54,945 --> 00:37:56,375
Is doing this to me "overreacting?"

446
00:37:56,745 --> 00:37:59,585
So those guys you know just kidnapped me
as a group because they were bored?

447
00:37:59,745 --> 00:38:00,845
And then did this to me?

448
00:38:02,485 --> 00:38:05,055
- You provoked them!
- I don't know what you told them,

449
00:38:05,825 --> 00:38:06,955
but they completely lost it.

450
00:38:07,425 --> 00:38:09,025
Did you or did you not hear...

451
00:38:09,025 --> 00:38:10,225
four senior boys screaming
that I scratched your face...

452
00:38:10,225 --> 00:38:12,525
as they began to strip me and beat me?

453
00:38:13,295 --> 00:38:15,595
You were smiling, encouraging them
to "teach me a real lesson."

454
00:38:16,495 --> 00:38:18,205
Tae Ye Jeong hit me over the head
with a piece of lumber.

455
00:38:18,465 --> 00:38:20,235
Come feel my head and see how bad it is.

456
00:38:21,035 --> 00:38:22,535
You... You little...

457
00:38:22,805 --> 00:38:25,375
Did you not know your daughter was running
around doing things like this?

458
00:38:28,775 --> 00:38:29,775
Say something!

459
00:38:30,775 --> 00:38:31,785
I'm sorry.

460
00:38:33,115 --> 00:38:34,955
- Go to your room.
- No.

461
00:38:35,885 --> 00:38:37,415
I'm not done talking yet.

462
00:38:39,125 --> 00:38:40,225
I...

463
00:38:40,955 --> 00:38:42,295
know how to fight.

464
00:38:42,755 --> 00:38:45,125
For self-defense,
so I wouldn't just get beaten up.

465
00:38:46,225 --> 00:38:48,335
If I hadn't held back with every ounce
of my strength today,

466
00:38:49,135 --> 00:38:50,895
Tae Ye Jeong would be
in a full-body cast right now.

467
00:38:52,565 --> 00:38:53,805
Big deal.

468
00:38:54,535 --> 00:38:55,975
You always go around dropping
your dad's name, don't you?

469
00:38:56,705 --> 00:38:58,175
Saying he's a lawyer
at a big firm in Seoul.

470
00:38:58,675 --> 00:39:00,045
So who's going to sue you
after you beat them up?

471
00:39:00,875 --> 00:39:03,375
I know.
Teachers walk on eggshells around you.

472
00:39:04,415 --> 00:39:06,745
And you've got top thug Yoon Seong Tae
as your "husband."

473
00:39:06,745 --> 00:39:08,515
He's not my husband, you witch!

474
00:39:09,115 --> 00:39:10,115
Shut it.

475
00:39:10,385 --> 00:39:13,685
To think she was born
just to bring shame to this family.

476
00:39:15,025 --> 00:39:16,355
There are many other victims.

477
00:39:16,895 --> 00:39:19,165
And they will all carry
those deep scars for life.

478
00:39:20,325 --> 00:39:21,665
Okay, we understand.

479
00:39:22,265 --> 00:39:24,765
We'll punish her severely
so she never does it again.

480
00:39:25,405 --> 00:39:28,635
But it's the middle of the night,
and with his blood pressure...

481
00:39:28,705 --> 00:39:30,435
The reason I came all this way is this.

482
00:39:33,305 --> 00:39:35,145
I want you to hit her ten times,
right in front of me.

483
00:39:36,875 --> 00:39:41,185
Or, I'll hit her myself, just as much
as Seong Tae's crew hit me today,

484
00:39:41,485 --> 00:39:43,155
and I'll turn myself in to the police.

485
00:39:47,085 --> 00:39:48,095
To be honest,

486
00:39:49,155 --> 00:39:50,795
I don't really have much to live for.

487
00:39:53,395 --> 00:39:55,795
Just like Ye Jeong taunted me
and hit me where it hurt,

488
00:39:56,865 --> 00:39:58,335
my own parents abandoned me.

489
00:39:59,405 --> 00:40:01,505
So why would I have any will to live
or attachment to my life?

490
00:40:03,405 --> 00:40:06,705
I grew up never once getting
to say "Mom" or "Dad" like everyone else.

491
00:40:07,545 --> 00:40:10,315
Can any of you even imagine
how that feels?

492
00:40:12,615 --> 00:40:14,715
I only hit you back a few times
in self-defense.

493
00:40:15,255 --> 00:40:18,785
You got so mad over a couple of hits
you sent your thug "husband" after me.

494
00:40:19,985 --> 00:40:24,155
I don't know if he's really your man
or if it's just for show.

495
00:40:25,225 --> 00:40:27,125
You shouldn't just say things like that...

496
00:40:27,195 --> 00:40:29,565
You've done a fine job
raising your only daughter.

497
00:40:31,935 --> 00:40:33,465
Try to imagine how the kids...

498
00:40:34,235 --> 00:40:35,635
you tormented and beat up must feel.

499
00:40:36,735 --> 00:40:40,145
They've likely imagined tearing you apart
a thousand times over in their minds.

500
00:40:42,075 --> 00:40:43,245
Because that's what I was doing today.

501
00:40:45,585 --> 00:40:46,885
I barely held myself back...

502
00:40:48,315 --> 00:40:49,715
and came here to deal
with this rationally.

503
00:40:51,355 --> 00:40:52,425
I'm sorry.

504
00:40:52,555 --> 00:40:53,755
We understand, so please go.

505
00:40:54,655 --> 00:40:56,955
- Something like today will never...
- You can't even hit her ten times?

506
00:40:58,065 --> 00:41:00,995
We'll discuss it
and discipline her ourselves.

507
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:02,165
In front of me.

508
00:41:04,765 --> 00:41:05,765
Only then,

509
00:41:07,005 --> 00:41:08,175
I think I'll be able to live with this.

510
00:41:09,735 --> 00:41:11,245
Go get me something.

511
00:41:13,005 --> 00:41:14,005
Hurry up.

512
00:41:14,915 --> 00:41:17,715
There's nothing suitable here.
I'll have something prepared by tomorrow.

513
00:41:17,775 --> 00:41:20,015
- We have the golf club.
- Father!

514
00:41:20,285 --> 00:41:21,285
I was wrong!

515
00:41:21,355 --> 00:41:24,785
If saying you were wrong could erase
the scars and injuries I have,

516
00:41:25,825 --> 00:41:26,825
I'd accept your apology.

517
00:41:31,795 --> 00:41:34,635
You hit her ten times.

518
00:41:34,995 --> 00:41:38,605
- Father!
- You hit her ten times,

519
00:41:39,935 --> 00:41:41,775
and her father will get a beating from me.

520
00:41:43,105 --> 00:41:45,305
You need to see this with your own eyes.

521
00:41:45,445 --> 00:41:46,745
All because of this one girl!

522
00:41:46,805 --> 00:41:49,045
Grandfather, I'll turn over a new leaf.
Starting today.

523
00:41:49,115 --> 00:41:50,815
What exactly is your relationship
with that punk?

524
00:41:51,075 --> 00:41:52,285
You're not even dry behind the ears.

525
00:41:52,615 --> 00:41:54,515
Please, I swear.

526
00:41:54,585 --> 00:41:57,115
He just always acts like he's flirting.

527
00:41:57,355 --> 00:41:58,725
There's nothing going on between us.

528
00:41:58,725 --> 00:42:00,425
He's just a bodyguard.

529
00:42:00,525 --> 00:42:02,425
If my orphanage friend
hadn't been there today,

530
00:42:02,425 --> 00:42:03,855
who knows what would've happened?

531
00:42:03,925 --> 00:42:06,265
- They were trying to strip me...
- Hey! Get over here. Now.

532
00:42:06,325 --> 00:42:07,325
Dad, I'm sorry! I was wrong!

533
00:42:07,595 --> 00:42:10,695
- Honey.
- What a fine mess this family is in.

534
00:42:10,995 --> 00:42:13,005
You feed her well,
dress her in nice clothes,

535
00:42:13,205 --> 00:42:16,105
and you think just throwing money
at her studies is how you raise a child?

536
00:42:16,505 --> 00:42:17,505
Darn it.

537
00:42:17,775 --> 00:42:18,905
- Grandfather!
- Honey.

538
00:42:20,505 --> 00:42:22,575
- Grandfather.
- Father.

539
00:42:24,475 --> 00:42:26,515
No, honey, you have to stop him.

540
00:42:48,035 --> 00:42:49,335
Maybe it was karma,

541
00:42:50,975 --> 00:42:52,945
but two months later, Tae Ye Jeong died.

542
00:42:54,345 --> 00:42:56,045
At their vacation home on Jeju Island,

543
00:42:57,215 --> 00:42:58,385
on the beach right in front of the house.

544
00:43:02,915 --> 00:43:05,925
Because I didn't have parents
and grew up in an orphanage,

545
00:43:07,255 --> 00:43:10,455
I went through so much
and was always looked down on.

546
00:43:12,425 --> 00:43:14,965
Sometimes I wonder
if the expressions I show people...

547
00:43:15,695 --> 00:43:16,735
and the emotions I display...

548
00:43:17,795 --> 00:43:20,505
are all just an act.

549
00:43:23,505 --> 00:43:25,105
When I felt so worthless,

550
00:43:25,745 --> 00:43:27,675
there were people
who genuinely cared for me.

551
00:43:29,375 --> 00:43:30,375
There was An Hee,

552
00:43:31,945 --> 00:43:32,945
and there was you.

553
00:43:36,555 --> 00:43:39,055
An Hee took care of me
because we were in the same boat,

554
00:43:40,025 --> 00:43:41,025
but you...

555
00:43:42,255 --> 00:43:44,255
genuinely adored me when I was just a kid.

556
00:43:47,325 --> 00:43:49,565
It was the first time
I had ever really felt it.

557
00:43:50,065 --> 00:43:53,105
"Oh, so this is what it's like
to be adored."

558
00:43:54,935 --> 00:43:56,135
It was only for a few months, but...

559
00:44:00,845 --> 00:44:03,945
I've always missed that warmth.

560
00:44:04,915 --> 00:44:06,845
Thinking of it helped me
get through the hard times.

561
00:44:14,695 --> 00:44:15,695
So even if you...

562
00:44:16,725 --> 00:44:19,195
like and love a wicked witch,

563
00:44:21,465 --> 00:44:23,795
I feel like it's my place
to try to understand.

564
00:44:25,605 --> 00:44:27,105
Maybe no one else has to,

565
00:44:29,275 --> 00:44:30,275
but I do.

566
00:44:39,445 --> 00:44:40,445
I'll always...

567
00:44:42,055 --> 00:44:43,055
be by your side.

568
00:44:44,685 --> 00:44:46,285
We'll never be apart again.

569
00:44:48,195 --> 00:44:49,195
Forever?

570
00:44:51,055 --> 00:44:52,065
Forever.

571
00:44:53,465 --> 00:44:55,195
You don't have to force it.

572
00:44:56,365 --> 00:44:57,395
I'm not.

573
00:44:59,005 --> 00:45:02,635
My brother and I aren't related by blood,
but he's the only brother I have.

574
00:45:05,505 --> 00:45:06,505
It's the same with you.

575
00:45:09,115 --> 00:45:10,275
Just promise me one thing.

576
00:45:12,345 --> 00:45:13,385
What?

577
00:45:13,385 --> 00:45:14,785
When things get tough and you struggle,

578
00:45:16,285 --> 00:45:17,815
don't try to bear it all on your own.

579
00:45:19,055 --> 00:45:20,355
You've got me now.

580
00:45:21,655 --> 00:45:23,255
I'll be content with just having you...

581
00:45:24,455 --> 00:45:26,395
by my side or watching from afar.

582
00:45:28,195 --> 00:45:29,265
My dear Ba Ra...

583
00:45:30,565 --> 00:45:32,205
You've done so well for yourself.

584
00:45:34,335 --> 00:45:35,935
The more I think about it,
the prouder I am of you,

585
00:45:38,545 --> 00:45:39,545
and I'm so grateful.

586
00:45:45,685 --> 00:45:47,585
Why'd An Hee have to die,
leaving us behind?

587
00:45:48,555 --> 00:45:50,155
Imagine how great it would be
if he were with us now.

588
00:45:54,125 --> 00:45:55,495
I have a favor to ask, too.

589
00:45:57,155 --> 00:45:58,165
What is it?

590
00:45:58,765 --> 00:46:00,025
Live a long, long life.

591
00:46:01,895 --> 00:46:02,895
Promise me.

592
00:46:06,805 --> 00:46:07,805
All right.

593
00:46:08,775 --> 00:46:10,835
I have to grant any wish
my big girl asks of me.

594
00:46:12,945 --> 00:46:14,645
Just don't ask for the moon.

595
00:46:15,715 --> 00:46:17,475
Some things are just impossible.

596
00:46:32,195 --> 00:46:33,565
If you find her,

597
00:46:33,895 --> 00:46:35,935
tell her...

598
00:46:36,635 --> 00:46:37,635
that her mom was so, so sorry.

599
00:46:44,005 --> 00:46:46,345
You have to find her. No matter what.

600
00:46:58,055 --> 00:46:59,985
You've been on a real roll lately.

601
00:47:00,355 --> 00:47:02,225
It's been one Geum Ba Ra exclusive
after another.

602
00:47:08,125 --> 00:47:10,835
(A sentence can change the world.
Relentless pursuit of truth)

603
00:47:13,305 --> 00:47:14,305
Get in.

604
00:47:17,405 --> 00:47:19,105
(A sentence can change the world.
Relentless pursuit of truth)

605
00:47:19,605 --> 00:47:21,545
The other outlets are busy
just copying each other's stories,

606
00:47:24,215 --> 00:47:28,255
and since you're so short-staffed,
it must be hard just to keep up.

607
00:47:28,315 --> 00:47:29,315
You're doing a great job.

608
00:47:29,585 --> 00:47:30,585
Not at all, sir.

609
00:47:31,155 --> 00:47:32,555
I'm keeping an eye on you.

610
00:47:33,425 --> 00:47:34,425
Thank you, sir.

611
00:47:35,855 --> 00:47:38,765
Sorry, Yong Joong.
I just got an urgent assignment.

612
00:47:39,495 --> 00:47:40,925
Don't apologize to me.

613
00:47:43,065 --> 00:47:44,065
Okay?

614
00:47:45,165 --> 00:47:46,165
Alright.

615
00:47:46,665 --> 00:47:48,205
And you've picked up another cute habit.

616
00:47:50,905 --> 00:47:53,705
At some point,
you dropped the formalities with me.

617
00:47:54,575 --> 00:47:56,915
My gosh, what's gotten into me?

618
00:47:57,215 --> 00:47:58,215
That's why I like it.

619
00:47:59,185 --> 00:48:00,315
You think I'm a pushover, don't you?

620
00:48:00,915 --> 00:48:01,915
No, that's not it.

621
00:48:02,215 --> 00:48:03,215
Try that again.

622
00:48:04,855 --> 00:48:05,855
No.

623
00:48:05,855 --> 00:48:07,655
I'm the guy
you're most comfortable being with.

624
00:48:11,995 --> 00:48:12,995
Get back to it.

625
00:48:14,065 --> 00:48:15,235
Yes.

626
00:48:15,235 --> 00:48:16,395
"Yes?"

627
00:48:16,695 --> 00:48:17,965
Okay, Yong Joong.

628
00:48:19,505 --> 00:48:20,505
You hang up first.

629
00:48:21,305 --> 00:48:22,505
Here's your coffee.

630
00:49:00,175 --> 00:49:01,175
Welcome.

631
00:49:05,385 --> 00:49:06,385
Here...

632
00:49:07,915 --> 00:49:11,055
Should I put this in the fridge for now?
Is there room?

633
00:49:12,455 --> 00:49:14,625
I'll sort it out and put it away...

634
00:49:16,295 --> 00:49:17,355
Have you been eating properly?

635
00:49:19,025 --> 00:49:20,895
Don't you have anyone you can call?

636
00:49:21,695 --> 00:49:22,835
My manager stops by every now and then...

637
00:49:27,065 --> 00:49:28,065
What about Ju Shin?

638
00:49:29,735 --> 00:49:31,845
How about staying somewhere else
for a little while?

639
00:49:36,815 --> 00:49:37,875
We're...

640
00:49:38,885 --> 00:49:40,315
all in the same boat.

641
00:49:41,515 --> 00:49:43,655
Ju Shin, you,

642
00:49:44,485 --> 00:49:45,555
and me.

643
00:49:47,725 --> 00:49:48,855
Someone once said...

644
00:49:49,895 --> 00:49:51,655
that if you don't have parents,
you're an orphan.

645
00:49:53,025 --> 00:49:55,935
When did your parents pass away?

646
00:49:57,095 --> 00:49:58,805
My dad passed away
when I was in second grade.

647
00:50:00,165 --> 00:50:01,365
And my mom passed away
during my senior year of high school.

648
00:50:02,105 --> 00:50:04,275
So I know how you feel
better than anyone, Momo.

649
00:50:06,275 --> 00:50:07,745
I know how hard it must be
for you right now.

650
00:50:17,515 --> 00:50:20,555
When my mother passed away,
I couldn't even really cry.

651
00:50:22,425 --> 00:50:23,755
My brother cried a lot, though.

652
00:50:25,265 --> 00:50:26,825
Isn't this the part
where he gives me a hug?

653
00:50:37,175 --> 00:50:39,045
Did Ju Shin tell you about my brother?

654
00:50:41,175 --> 00:50:44,645
James told me himself once.

655
00:50:45,515 --> 00:50:47,985
That he was adopted in elementary school.

656
00:50:52,125 --> 00:50:55,455
I heard James's birth mother
and your mother...

657
00:50:56,295 --> 00:50:58,795
were in the same orchestra, right?

658
00:50:59,125 --> 00:51:00,125
Yes.

659
00:51:03,765 --> 00:51:05,365
It might sound like a cliche,
but it's true.

660
00:51:06,435 --> 00:51:07,735
As time goes on,

661
00:51:09,005 --> 00:51:10,435
the sadness does fade.

662
00:51:12,445 --> 00:51:14,145
For now, all you can do is endure it.

663
00:51:14,675 --> 00:51:15,875
There's no other way.

664
00:51:19,815 --> 00:51:20,885
Thank you.

665
00:51:31,555 --> 00:51:34,765
I bought the Laketop penthouse.
Would you like to stay there for a while?

666
00:51:35,595 --> 00:51:36,835
What's the point of leaving it empty?

667
00:51:36,835 --> 00:51:39,105
I was worried tenants would ruin it,
so it's empty.

668
00:51:40,405 --> 00:51:43,605
The 18-million-dollar Laketop penthouse?

669
00:51:49,145 --> 00:51:50,175
Goodbye.

670
00:51:50,415 --> 00:51:51,885
Think about it and text me.

671
00:51:53,685 --> 00:51:54,685
Okay.

672
00:52:14,035 --> 00:52:15,175
Yes!

673
00:52:20,605 --> 00:52:23,615
That was the most delicious breakfast
I've had in a long time.

674
00:52:23,875 --> 00:52:24,945
Thank you.

675
00:52:29,285 --> 00:52:32,355
- What's got you in such a good mood?
- It's Ms. Geum Ba Ra.

676
00:52:32,685 --> 00:52:34,025
She said she loved my cooking.

677
00:52:34,085 --> 00:52:37,225
You would've made a killing
in the restaurant business.

678
00:52:37,495 --> 00:52:39,625
You dote on your brother,

679
00:52:39,625 --> 00:52:40,995
so no wonder
he doesn't think about getting married.

680
00:52:41,295 --> 00:52:42,495
He has everything he needs.

681
00:52:43,835 --> 00:52:45,735
How many of our pieces got into
Sera Lauren magazine?

682
00:52:48,575 --> 00:52:50,505
(Ha Yong Joong, CEO of WorldNet)

683
00:52:53,945 --> 00:52:57,515
(Ha Yong Joong, Developer of
Record-Breaking Mega-Hit "Lost Knights")

684
00:53:03,355 --> 00:53:04,385
(Ba Ra)

685
00:53:04,485 --> 00:53:06,125
I know this must be really hard,

686
00:53:06,885 --> 00:53:08,625
but people are curious.

687
00:53:09,195 --> 00:53:11,925
So it'd be good to briefly announce
your future plans.

688
00:53:12,725 --> 00:53:14,625
That should quiet down the media, too.

689
00:53:15,565 --> 00:53:17,365
I can drop by for a bit,

690
00:53:17,765 --> 00:53:19,735
or we could meet somewhere
you're comfortable.

691
00:53:23,105 --> 00:53:24,275
Are you getting any sleep?

692
00:53:25,775 --> 00:53:28,545
Only a little after I've completely
exhausted myself.

693
00:53:30,215 --> 00:53:31,515
Are you cleaning up her things alone?

694
00:53:34,385 --> 00:53:35,715
I'd like to help.

695
00:53:36,455 --> 00:53:37,455
I'm okay.

696
00:53:39,585 --> 00:53:41,355
Last year, on the day we were
supposed to meet,

697
00:53:41,755 --> 00:53:44,525
I saw your mother at the airport,
and she was so cheerful.

698
00:53:45,865 --> 00:53:48,295
Did you have any idea she was struggling?

699
00:53:52,105 --> 00:53:54,805
Then why did you cut off all contact
for so long...

700
00:53:56,205 --> 00:53:59,475
The moment I let my guard down,
I got burnt out.

701
00:54:01,145 --> 00:54:02,975
I spent a few months in Lausanne, too.

702
00:54:04,515 --> 00:54:05,645
Lausanne, in Switzerland?

703
00:54:09,015 --> 00:54:10,455
I need you to run a story
on my retirement.

704
00:54:12,085 --> 00:54:14,325
Wouldn't it be better to keep busy?

705
00:54:15,255 --> 00:54:16,395
I don't have it in me.

706
00:54:16,925 --> 00:54:17,925
Who would I even be doing it for...?

707
00:54:18,795 --> 00:54:20,425
Your fans are going to be so disappointed.

708
00:54:23,095 --> 00:54:25,065
Is your wedding with Director Shin
still on?

709
00:54:26,665 --> 00:54:28,105
You don't have to talk about it
if you don't want to.

710
00:54:28,905 --> 00:54:30,475
It's just so absurd.

711
00:54:31,175 --> 00:54:32,745
Professor Shin, who was so healthy...

712
00:54:36,315 --> 00:54:39,715
I mean, Ju Shin's father
passed away so suddenly,

713
00:54:40,645 --> 00:54:41,745
and now my mom, too.

714
00:54:44,615 --> 00:54:46,425
Does your head hurt?
Should I get you something for it?

715
00:54:46,425 --> 00:54:47,525
No, I have some.

716
00:54:48,125 --> 00:54:50,625
I'm not in a good state,
so if I'm not around much...

717
00:54:52,765 --> 00:54:54,995
I understand. Take your time to heal.

718
00:54:57,095 --> 00:54:58,365
Yong Joong stopped by, didn't he?

719
00:54:59,605 --> 00:55:01,265
Are you that close? Are you dating?

720
00:55:03,575 --> 00:55:07,275
He's an old friend from the orphanage.
We were best friends in high school.

721
00:55:07,905 --> 00:55:09,745
I've told you this before.

722
00:55:14,115 --> 00:55:15,985
My brain is completely fried.

723
00:55:17,115 --> 00:55:18,615
I even forget to eat.

724
00:55:31,195 --> 00:55:33,905
To be honest,
her condition was critical at first.

725
00:55:34,065 --> 00:55:37,035
She only recovered because Director Shin
kept her on hyperbaric oxygen therapy.

726
00:55:37,435 --> 00:55:38,535
How bad was it?

727
00:55:38,745 --> 00:55:41,305
I never saw her myself.
I heard it from one of the executives.

728
00:55:42,075 --> 00:55:43,445
Is she really going to retire?

729
00:55:44,245 --> 00:55:47,585
Yes.
Has Director Choi told you differently?

730
00:55:48,545 --> 00:55:49,555
(Ha Yong Joong: "Lost Knights" Creator)

731
00:55:49,615 --> 00:55:51,455
(Actress Momo Suddenly Retires.
Agency Respects Her Wishes.)

732
00:55:51,555 --> 00:55:53,025
Looks like Geum Ba Ra
landed another scoop.

733
00:55:53,485 --> 00:55:55,625
- What is it?
- Momo announced her retirement.

734
00:55:55,955 --> 00:55:56,955
My gosh!

735
00:55:57,455 --> 00:56:00,165
(Actress Momo, 26, suddenly announced
her retirement from acting this afternoon)

736
00:56:00,225 --> 00:56:03,295
(Nua General Hospital)

737
00:56:03,365 --> 00:56:05,535
(Nua General Hospital)

738
00:56:05,605 --> 00:56:06,705
(Neurosurgery)

739
00:56:14,845 --> 00:56:18,675
Could you please give this
to Director Shin?

740
00:56:34,325 --> 00:56:35,535
Do you like the painting?

741
00:56:37,695 --> 00:56:39,165
It's a Paul Kim, isn't it?

742
00:56:43,735 --> 00:56:44,905
Take that painting down.

743
00:56:45,845 --> 00:56:47,805
- Why? It's a nice piece.
- I'm giving it to Reporter Geum.

744
00:56:51,875 --> 00:56:52,885
Hey.

745
00:56:55,045 --> 00:56:56,555
You don't have feelings for Ba Ra, do you?

746
00:57:01,725 --> 00:57:04,025
- You do?
- I've thought about it.

747
00:57:04,825 --> 00:57:06,665
You know I have a thing for smart women.

748
00:57:07,125 --> 00:57:08,195
Are you crazy?

749
00:57:08,765 --> 00:57:11,095
Are you out of your mind? You're 50!

750
00:57:11,195 --> 00:57:12,335
So what if I'm 50?

751
00:57:12,465 --> 00:57:14,265
Age is just a number.

752
00:57:14,265 --> 00:57:15,305
It's a very important number.

753
00:57:15,365 --> 00:57:17,935
People think I'm in my late thirties.

754
00:57:18,775 --> 00:57:19,975
You believe that flattery?

755
00:57:19,975 --> 00:57:22,245
In ten years, you'll be 60.

756
00:57:22,315 --> 00:57:24,245
- And Ba Ra's in her 30s.
- Her late 30s.

757
00:57:24,975 --> 00:57:27,785
Snap out of it.
She's not the right person for you.

758
00:57:27,885 --> 00:57:29,115
Don't you even think about it.

759
00:57:30,815 --> 00:57:32,485
There are plenty of other smart women
out there.

760
00:57:32,955 --> 00:57:35,595
Professor Lee Jin Hee, Dr. Shin...
Didn't you say they were both interested?

761
00:57:35,655 --> 00:57:37,025
But I'm the one who has to be attracted.

762
00:57:37,895 --> 00:57:39,425
That's greedy.

763
00:57:39,425 --> 00:57:41,095
How could you go for Ba Ra?
She could be your daughter.

764
00:57:41,265 --> 00:57:43,335
Look at actors in Hollywood.
It's the new trend.

765
00:57:43,765 --> 00:57:46,665
Find a better trend to follow.
You're no Hollywood star.

766
00:57:46,735 --> 00:57:47,935
Hey, I'm quite the catch.

767
00:57:48,535 --> 00:57:51,305
James of Lim Company.
Everyone in the industry knows who I am.

768
00:57:51,675 --> 00:57:53,945
Please stop. Don't embarrass yourself.

769
00:57:54,205 --> 00:57:56,015
Fortune favors the bold.

770
00:57:56,075 --> 00:57:57,645
- James.
- You just don't want to have...

771
00:57:57,645 --> 00:57:59,215
to call her your sister-in-law, do you?

772
00:57:59,815 --> 00:58:01,045
You've really got a problem.

773
00:58:01,615 --> 00:58:04,885
That's rich. You fell head over heels
for your best friend's fiancee.

774
00:58:04,955 --> 00:58:05,985
It's not like I knew who she was!

775
00:58:06,655 --> 00:58:08,655
Either way, don't drag me into this mess.

776
00:58:10,795 --> 00:58:14,725
How'd you feel if a woman 23 years older
than you threw herself at you?

777
00:58:14,795 --> 00:58:16,195
It's different for men and women.

778
00:58:16,965 --> 00:58:18,595
You'll get torn to shreds if you do that.

779
00:58:23,005 --> 00:58:25,405
I don't care if they drag me
through the mud.

780
00:58:28,405 --> 00:58:31,515
(True correction, bright future)

781
00:58:51,735 --> 00:58:54,705
Before my mom passed away,

782
00:58:54,805 --> 00:58:57,075
she told me I had an older sister.

783
00:58:57,975 --> 00:58:59,105
It was like a deathbed confession.

784
00:59:01,275 --> 00:59:03,345
Back when you two were in high school.

785
00:59:06,915 --> 00:59:08,415
So you haven't found her yet?

786
00:59:11,585 --> 00:59:12,785
It's not that simple.

787
00:59:14,485 --> 00:59:15,555
In any case,

788
00:59:16,755 --> 00:59:19,195
I've never met her,
but you're my sister's father,

789
00:59:20,025 --> 00:59:21,525
and you used to be my mom's boyfriend.

790
00:59:22,795 --> 00:59:24,035
You don't have to be so formal with me.

791
00:59:28,105 --> 00:59:29,175
Did that...

792
00:59:30,035 --> 00:59:31,575
cause any conflict?

793
00:59:32,405 --> 00:59:33,405
No.

794
00:59:33,805 --> 00:59:36,215
It's not my place
to say anything about the past.

795
00:59:37,045 --> 00:59:38,275
I admit I was surprised.

796
00:59:39,545 --> 00:59:41,845
My father was much older than she was,

797
00:59:41,985 --> 00:59:44,385
so I had a vague inkling...

798
00:59:44,685 --> 00:59:45,955
that there was a backstory.

799
00:59:48,855 --> 00:59:50,725
If by some miracle we find her,

800
00:59:51,755 --> 00:59:56,265
I'd like to get along as sisters,
not just because my mom wanted us to.

801
00:59:56,795 --> 00:59:59,665
She's my only blood relative, after all.

802
01:00:01,135 --> 01:00:02,135
So please, let me know.

803
01:00:07,945 --> 01:00:09,045
You don't have to see me out.

804
01:00:32,465 --> 01:00:34,005
(Investigator Park)

805
01:00:42,845 --> 01:00:43,845
Hello?

806
01:00:44,815 --> 01:00:46,245
I believe we've found your daughter.

807
01:00:48,915 --> 01:00:49,915
Really?

808
01:01:15,475 --> 01:01:18,275
(Doctor Shin)

809
01:01:18,545 --> 01:01:19,545
Ladies first.

810
01:01:19,945 --> 01:01:21,415
This is our first day as a couple.

811
01:01:21,715 --> 01:01:23,515
- This is a bit of a weak celebration.
- It's more than enough.

812
01:01:23,585 --> 01:01:24,585
So I'm your number one?

813
01:01:25,355 --> 01:01:28,055
Don't tell me it's that Kim Jin Ju.

814
01:01:28,625 --> 01:01:31,055
- You're friends with Geum Ba Ra?
- Yes.

815
01:01:31,055 --> 01:01:32,395
Are both of you still single?

816
01:01:32,695 --> 01:01:34,665
- A boyfriend.
- Right.

817
01:01:34,725 --> 01:01:38,095
What if I only had eyes
for Director Shin Ju Shin?

818
01:01:38,165 --> 01:01:40,765
Shin Ju Shin is someone
women would fall for.

819
01:01:40,835 --> 01:01:43,775
- He's got it all.
- Hello, sir.

820
01:01:43,835 --> 01:01:45,235
You should brace yourself.

821
01:01:45,235 --> 01:01:46,245
Can I see her today?

822
01:01:46,305 --> 01:01:48,345
Is it because I'm thinking
about Momo too much?

823
01:01:48,975 --> 01:01:49,975
Sir.

824
01:01:51,645 --> 01:01:55,345
I just wish I had someone
I could give my all to.

825
01:01:55,585 --> 01:01:57,485
I gave you my heart

826
01:01:58,655 --> 01:02:00,925
I gave you my tears

827
01:02:01,485 --> 01:02:04,155
And I gave you my dreams

828
01:02:09,895 --> 01:02:11,865
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
